You are receiving this crime warning as part of Old Dominion University's commitment to provide campus-area crime information, and as part of our compliance with the federal Clery Act (Jeanne Clery Disclosure of Campus Security Policy and Campus Crime Statistics Act).
REPORTED OFFENSE: The Old Dominion University Police Department is investigating an armed robbery which occurred at approximately 7:30 p.m. on November 12 in the 1000 block of 49th Street, in Norfolk. A person walking alone on W. 49th Street was approached by two (2) males; one of which displayed a handgun while the other suspect grabbed personal property from the individual before fleeing the area. Both males were last seen leaving in a silver 4-door mid-size vehicle heading east on 48th Street towards Killam Avenue. The victim was not injured.